modules.description: Computes cryptographic hashes using the BLAKE3 algorithm, supporting incremental updates and finalization. It operates on byte sequences and binary data, providing fixed-size output hashes. Used for generating secure checksums in data integrity verification and digital signatures.

Computes cryptographic hashes of byte sequences using the Blake3 algorithm, supporting both single-threaded and multi-core execution. Accepts a digest size in bytes and a source byte string, returning the computed hash. Used for generating secure checksums in distributed systems and data integrity verification.
